  "description": "Fix GitHub Pages Deployment Path Configuration\n\nResolve 404 errors on GitHub Pages deployment caused by incorrect asset path references in the wesole_nutki website.\n\nProblem:\nStatic assets (CSS and JavaScript files) are failing to load with 404 errors due to duplicated path segments in URLs (e.g., /wesole_nutki/wesole_nutki/ instead of /wesole_nutki/).\n\nRequirements:\n- Investigate base URL configuration in the site generator or build tool (Hugo, Jekyll, etc.)\n- Correct the baseURL or publicPath setting to match GitHub Pages repository structure\n- Verify asset path generation removes the duplicate /wesole_nutki/ directory reference\n- Rebuild and redeploy the site to GitHub Pages\n- Test all affected resources load correctly:\n  * style.min.338bd0ca61754884d1ae2ea296a84b75bbd045df2ac61c820201736102fe66ef.css\n  * glightbox.min.min.9961219639aa1b1bc73b0871fb62a7ae5d196bd874155d9c09f284bf11a66839.css\n  * bundle.02c579cb5d066be6659a8af0fdbe68aecc966cd2e65c72582734efeafe7a0d3f.js\n- Verify the site renders correctly at https://bartusiak.ai/wesole_nutki/\n- Check for any additional broken links or asset references throughout the site\n\n\nseems like it doubles the path wesole_nutki",
